The Ministry of Foreign Affairs, has announced the passing away of the Nigerian Ambassador to Qatar, Abdullahi Bawa Wase. A WhatsApp message issued by the spokesman of the Ministry, Tiwa- Tope Elias on Saturday, noted that Ambassador Bawa, a non-career Ambassador, from Plateau State,Â  has been sick for a while until his death on Friday night. The statement noted that the Minister of Foreign Affairs, Geoffrey Onyeama, received the news of his death with shock and prayed that God grant his family and the Nation the fortitude to bear the great loss. The late ambassador is to be buried in Doha, Qatar at 7.00 pm(local time) today, Saturday, the statement added. 